      "content": "Ah, the perplexing world of student loans, where the principal and interest dance a slow, intricate ballet. Imagine you're a brave knight, valiantly battling the dragon of debt, but the beast only shrinks a little with each swing of your sword. That's your principal, and the dragon's fiery breath is the interest.\n\nEvery month, you give the dragon a portion of your treasure, but a chunk of it goes to feeding the beast. The interest is like the dragon's appetite, always growing, even as you chip away at the dragon's size. The principal, the dragon's actual body, only shrinks when you manage to slay a significant part of it, which is harder than it seems.\n\nSo, when you pay the same amount every month, it's like trying to feed the dragon with a steady stream of gold. The dragon's appetite (interest) keeps growing, and the dragon's body (principal) only shrinks when you manage to slay a big chunk of it. It's a slow, steady battle, but don't lose hope. With time and persistence, you'll eventually slay the dragon and be free of debt. Keep fighting, brave knight!",
